==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Renunciation
<hw>Re*nun`ci*a"tion</hw> <pr>(r?-n?n`s?-?"sh?n ⟦or⟧ -sh?-?"sh?n;
277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>renonciation</ets>, L.
<ets>renuntiatio</ets> ann announcement. See <er>Renounce</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of renouncing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>Formal declination to take out
letters of administration, or to assume an office, privilege, or
right.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Renouncement; disownment; disavowal; disavowment;
disclaimer; rejection; abjuration; recantation; denial; abandonment;
relinquishment.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1219 --></p>

<p><ent>Renunciatory</ent>⟦br⟧
